<br /><span style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(51, 102, 255); text-decoration: underline;">Admin Panel</span><br /><br /><span style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255); font-weight: bold;">Online Test</span><br /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Available</span> : Under available option there are the tests which are already created .In created tests we can edit the tests and we can enable or disable any particular test . Also we can delete any test and we can check the total number of questions of any test.</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Create&nbsp; new:</span> In create new option there is test configuration. </span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">&nbsp;Test name: In create new option we can give name to any test.</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">&nbsp;Time:After then we can give maximum time for test and minimum passing &nbsp; &nbsp; marks of the test.</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">Description: In description we can give any notice to the user before start the&nbsp;&nbsp; test.</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">Assign group: Assign test to available group</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">Attach file:Attach file with question. supported format is jpg, gif, flv, swf,&nbsp; mp3, txt and wmv</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">Next there is option available to edit&nbsp; test configuration and add questions for the test.</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(51, 102, 255);">Member:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Activate new</span> : In this option you can activate the new member (if you selected conformation option by administrator is basic setting module).</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Member list: </span>In this option there is list of all the members available and there is option on the top to search any member who is already joined and also you can remove any member from the list, view their detail and temporarily deactivate them. &nbsp; .</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Deactivated:</span> In this option you can check the list of deactivated members.</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(51, 102, 255);">Result/Report :</span></span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">View result:</span> In this option first of all you have to select the group of which you want to see the result. After click on next you will get the history of test and can view the result of all members of that group.</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Generate report:</span> In this option after selecting group and test name we can generate report of test.</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(51, 102, 255);">Security:</span> </span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Hacker detected:</span> Script can detect the member who tried to attempt any hacking in this script. After detecting the hacker you can remove him from the members list or the temporary deactivated.</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Database backup:</span> Under this option we can make the backup of all the data for restore in future by specific date .</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(51, 102, 255);">Group:</span> </span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Create new:</span> Here we can create a new group by giving a specific name to the group. For example if this application is used for any school then administrator can create a group by giving the class name or standered name.</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">View group:</span> In this option we can view the groups which are already created.</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(51, 102, 255);">Operator:</span>&nbsp; </span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Create new: </span>In this option we can generate new operator by giving particular id, password and also assign to specific group . operator can only create test for&nbsp; given group and access the member and result area</span> <span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">of that group.</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">View operators:</span> In this option we can check the list of operators and we can remove any operator from the list.</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(51, 102, 255);">Settings: </span></span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Basic: </span>Here we can give the title to all the web pages. </span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">in footer text we can give the our company name or website link .</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">In member conformation we can select the required method to conform the registration of the members.</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">In mandatory field we can select the option required for the registration of new member.</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Banner :</span> Here we can upload or change the banner of the application .</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Password : </span>In this option we can change our password or reset the password.</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><br /><span style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(51, 102, 255);">Help: </span></span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Script help:</span>&nbsp; We can read the documentation for the useage of script.</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Report error:</span> In this option we can send the report of any error if occurred in the script . Our supporting team will we contact you by email to fix the error.</span><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><br style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);" /><br /> 









